The paper deals with the problem of learning from synthesized data in the context of computer vision, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of deep learning techniques, which further supports this assumption. Additionally, the paper involves the formulation of an online communication process between a classifier and a sampler, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of synthesized data, which suggests that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of ShapeNet models, which suggests that it may belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the exploration of an infinite data space, which suggests that it may also belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
